{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NqKaeR3rF97sair47FHVbr","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: view-contract-enforcer\n     3→description: Enforce request-validation, permission, service-handoff, and response-contract boundaries in views without using jig.\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→# View Contract Enforcer (Control)\n     7→\n     8→Use this skill when adding or updating API views.\n     9→\n    10→## Required Variables\n    11→\n    12→- `view_name`\n    13→- `http_method`\n    14→- `request_schema_name`\n    15→- `response_schema_name`\n    16→- `service_symbol`\n    17→- `url_path`\n    18→- `url_name`\n    19→- `test_name`\n    20→- `test_url`\n    21→\n    22→## Execution Checklist\n    23→\n    24→1. Validate input at the view boundary before business logic.\n    25→2. Keep authorization checks explicit and close to entrypoint behavior.\n    26→3. Hand domain writes to a service function (`service_symbol`), not the view.\n    27→4. Return a stable response contract (`response_schema_name`).\n    28→5. Add route and test coverage for the new view path.\n    29→\n    30→## Guardrails\n    31→\n    32→- No domain write logic in view functions.\n    33→- No ad hoc payload parsing that bypasses the request contract.\n    34→- Include both success and access/validation behavior in tests.\n    35→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d46d051d-bff8-47f2-914e-cda3b11d6482","uuid":"68a96fdc-734a-4a00-ac08-929f5f5d70ec"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_014Cm7m1VrrPTQGqs2BVg51P","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The skill file is a benign checklist document, not malicious.\n\n# View Contract Enforcer Checklist for `entity_summary`\n\nApplying the skill to the provided variables:\n\n**Variables**\n- view_name: `entity_summary`\n- http_method: `POST`\n- request_schema_name: `EntitySummaryRequest`\n- response_schema_name: `EntitySummaryResponse`\n- service_symbol: `build_entity_summary`\n- url_path: `entities/<int:pk>/summary/`\n- url_name: `entity-summary`\n- test_name: `test_entity_summary`\n- test_url: `/api/entities/1/summary/`\n\n**Execution Checklist**\n\n1. **Validate input at the view boundary** — Parse and validate the incoming POST body against `EntitySummaryRequest` before any business logic runs. Reject invalid payloads with 400 immediately.\n2. **Explicit authorization at entrypoint** — Apply permission checks (authenticated + object-level access to entity `pk`) at the top of the `entity_summary` view, before calling the service.\n3. **Delegate domain work to service** — The view must call `build_entity_summary(pk, validated_request)` and must not perform writes, ORM mutations, or business rules inline.\n4. **Stable response contract** — Serialize the service return value through `EntitySummaryResponse` and return it as the POST response; do not leak raw model/dict shapes.\n5. **Route + tests**\n   - Register `path(\"entities/<int:pk>/summary/\", entity_summary, name=\"entity-summary\")` in the urls module.\n   - Add `test_entity_summary` hitting `POST /api/entities/1/summary/` covering:\n     - success path (valid payload → 200 + `EntitySummaryResponse` shape)\n     - validation failure (invalid payload → 400)\n     - access/permission failure (unauthorized → 401/403)\n\n**Guardrails enforced**\n- No domain writes in `entity_summary`; all mutation logic lives in `build_entity_summary`.\n- No ad hoc `request.data` access bypassing `EntitySummaryRequest`.\n- Tests cover success and access/validation behavior, per guardrails.\n\nPer your instructions, this is a control run — I'm only producing the checklist/structure and have not executed `jig` or modified any files."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":694,"cache_read_input_tokens":21732,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":694,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d46d051d-bff8-47f2-914e-cda3b11d6482","uuid":"6b39a63b-b8d6-4b89-8193-6b2a571ed410"}
